{"id":"beyond","term":"Beyond","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>When used with reference to Jordan, signifies in the writings of Moses the west side of the river, as he wrote on the east bank (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 50:10\">Gen. 50:10</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 50:11\">11</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Deuteronomy 1:1\">Deut. 1:1</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:5\">5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 3:8\">3:8</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 3:20\">20</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 5:20\">4:46</a>); but in the writings of Joshua, after he had crossed the river, it means the east side (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 5:1\">Josh. 5:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 12:7\">12:7</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Joshua 22:7\">22:7</a>).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Genesis 50:10","Genesis 50:11","Deuteronomy 1:1","Genesis 1:5","Genesis 3:8","Genesis 3:20","Genesis 5:20","Joshua 5:1","Joshua 12:7","Joshua 22:7"]}